      <section id="id15870742">
        <title>[LO 2.2; LO 2.3]</title>
        <para id="id21443515">QUESTIONS</para>
        <list id="id10357169" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic">
          <item>What is an ECOLOGICAL ENVIRONMENT?</item>
        </list>
        <para id="id6221471"/>
        <para id="id12203512"/>
        <para id="id13700082">2. What, are the basic components or parts of all ecological environments?</para>
        <para id="id6166351"/>
        <para id="id6166354"/>
        <para id="id16697930">3. <emphasis effect="italics">Bios</emphasis> is the Greek word for <emphasis effect="italics">Life</emphasis>.</para>
        <para id="id15624173">What, do you think, the following concepts mean? (Ask your teacher to explain.)</para>
        <para id="id16417463">3.1  <emphasis effect="bold">abiotic </emphasis></para>
        <para id="id12024379">3.2  <emphasis effect="bold">biotic </emphasis></para>
        <para id="id20510530">3.3  <emphasis effect="bold">factor </emphasis></para>
        <para id="id3287399"/>
        <para id="id13709641">4. An ecological environment can be described as an ECOSYSTEM.</para>
        <para id="id4540134">4.1 An ecosystem is </para>
        <para id="id15641921"/>
        <para id="id15641924"/>
        <para id="id19593295">An <emphasis effect="bold">ECOSYSTEM</emphasis> is, the living and non-living components of a certain environment and the interaction between the components.</para>
        <para id="id19928502">The study of ecosystems and the interactions between the organisms and their environment is called <emphasis effect="bold">ECOLOGY</emphasis>.</para>
      </section>
